[^30]: Edelkamp, Stefan; Weiß, Armin (7–8 January 2019). *Worst-Case Efficient Sorting with QuickMergesort*. ALENEX 2019: 21st Workshop on Algorithm Engineering and Experiments. San Diego. [arXiv](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ArXiv_\\(identifier\\) "ArXiv (identifier)"):[1811.99833](https://arxiv.org/abs/1811.99833). [doi](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doi_\\(identifier\\) "Doi (identifier)"):[10.1137/1.9781611975499.1](https://doi.org/10.1137%2F1.9781611975499.1). [ISBN](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISBN_\\(identifier\\) "ISBN (identifier)") [978-1-61197-549-9](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-61197-549-9 "Special:BookSources/978-1-61197-549-9"). on small instances Heapsort is already considerably slower than Quicksort (in our experiments more than 30% for *n* = 2 <sup>10</sup>) and on larger instances it suffers from its poor cache behavior (in our experiments more than eight times slower than Quicksort for sorting 2 <sup>28</sup> elements).

